% Budget/contract: 0.6 page. Four paper-facing families only: TCN primary,
% standard-DLinear, MS-DLinear+TCN, and LightGBM. MLP appears only as a
% train-inner control row where needed; do not present LSTM as a route model.
% Source: protocol 02 + configs/models/.
\section{Models}

The roster exists to drive the protocol, and only the TCN is primary. We score
four families: a temporal convolutional network, a decomposition-linear model, a
decomposition-convolutional hybrid, and gradient-boosted trees
\cite{bai2018empirical,zeng2023dlinear,ke2017lightgbm,grinsztajn2022tree}. None
is a known-signal positive control, so the roster can show that the protocol does
not manufacture an edge on a near-null case, but it cannot show that the protocol
would catch a real one.

The predeclared primary is a temporal convolutional network
\cite{bai2018empirical} in a \texttt{tcn\_tiny} configuration: two residual
blocks of 16 channels each, kernel size \(2\), and learning rate \(10^{-3}\).
Standard DLinear (Std-DLinear) splits each input window into trend and residual
components and feeds each to its own linear head before summing them
\cite{zeng2023dlinear}. The hybrid pairs a multi-scale DLinear branch
(MS-DLinear) with a small residual TCN branch (together, MS-DLinear+TCN) and is
a roster alternative, not a contributed model; its MS-DLinear branch combines
several decomposition kernels in the manner of series-decomposition forecasters
\cite{wu2021autoformer,zhou2022fedformer}. The fourth family is LightGBM
\cite{ke2017lightgbm}, a gradient-boosted tree run as a tabular baseline on
windowed features \cite{grinsztajn2022tree}.

Predeclaration covers the roster and the primary-versus-fallback rule, and the
train-inner search completes before either readout opens. The search fits the TCN
configuration above and holds LightGBM in reserve as the primary-slot fallback
for mechanical or reconstruction failures. None occurred,
so the fallback never fired. The frozen specification then enters both readouts
unchanged, and neither readout selects a final model. On the guarded row-pooled
mean some roster alternatives post numerically higher deltas than the TCN
primary, but only post hoc and not like-for-like; the TCN is the lone
pre-committed frozen primary. No recurrent model enters the roster, and the
last-step multilayer perceptron (\texttt{last\_step\_mlp}) appears only as a
train-inner control, never as a scored family. The four families share the data,
seeds, and frozen designation that the next section fixes.
